         <abstract>
            <p>Let m &gt; 2, ζ&lt;sub&gt;m&lt;/sub&gt; an m-th primitive root of 1, q &lt;tex-math&gt;$\equiv$&lt;/tex-math&gt; 1 mod 2m a prime number, s = s&lt;sub&gt;q&lt;/sub&gt; a primitive root modulo q and f = f&lt;sub&gt;q&lt;/sub&gt; = (q - 1)/m. We study the Jacobi sums J&lt;sub&gt;a,b&lt;/sub&gt; = - ∑&lt;sup&gt;q-1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;k=2&lt;/sub&gt; ζ&lt;sup&gt;a ind&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt;(k) + b ind&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt; (1 - k)&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;m&lt;/sub&gt;, 0 ≤ a, b ≤ m - 1, where ind&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt; (k) is the least nonnegative integer such that s&lt;tex-math&gt;$^{ind_s(k)} \equiv$&lt;/tex-math&gt; k mod q. We exhibit a set of properties that characterize these sums, some congruences they satisfy, and a MAPLE program to calculate them. Then we use those results to show how one can construct families Pq(x), q ∈ P, of irreducible polynomials of Gaussian periods, η&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; = ∑&lt;sup&gt;f - 1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;j = 0&lt;/sub&gt; ζ&lt;sup&gt;s&lt;sup&gt;i+mj&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;q&lt;/sub&gt;, of degree m, where P is a suitable set of primes &lt;tex-math&gt;$\equiv$&lt;/tex-math&gt; 1 mod 2m. We exhibit examples of such families for several small values of m, and give a MAPLE program to construct more of them.</p>
          </abstract>
